What is the duration between 19 May 2963, 21:51 and 10 August 2963, 14:33? Please answer in D days, HH:MM:SS.
Enclose final answer within triple angle brackets, like <<<the answer>>>.

from datetime import datetime

# Define the two dates
date1 = datetime(2963, 5, 19, 21, 51)
date2 = datetime(2963, 8, 10, 14, 33)

# Calculate the difference
duration = date2 - date1

# Format the duration in D days, HH:MM:SS
duration_str = f"{duration.days} days, {duration.seconds // 3600:02}:{(duration.seconds % 3600) // 60:02}:{duration.seconds % 60:02}"
duration_str
